\subsubsection{Biomass and stock status}

The following present marginal posterior distributions characterizing the major herring stocks for the following parameters and derived quantities: recruitment, instantaneous natural mortality, biomass reconstructions and stock depletion.
To help readers view and interpret trends in results and uncertainty for each stock major stock area, collective sets of figures showing these four sets of model results across the \Sexpr{min(yrRange)} to \Sexpr{max(yrRange)} time series are presented by stock area in Figures \ref{figStoryboard\Sexpr{mNames[1]}\Sexpr{allRegions$major[1]}} to \ref{figStoryboard\Sexpr{mNames[length(mNames)]}\Sexpr{allRegions$major[length(allRegions$major)]}}.
The following sections also present maximum posterior density (MPD) estimates characterizing the major herring stocks for: spawn survey scaling parameter ($q$), age-2 recruits versus spawning biomass relationships, age-specific fishing gear selectivity, and total instantaneous mortality.
To enable readers to compare trends between major stock areas, results for each of these types of MPD estimates for all major stock areas in the 1951-2014 times series are shown together in individual figures.

